   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 5 - Design Decisions & Transferability\n",
    "\n",
    "| Decision | Rationale |\n",
    "|----------|-----------|\n",
    "| **Shortcodes bypass LLM** | Restaurant ops commands are high-frequency and time-sensitive. Shortcodes eliminate API latency and cost for ~80% of traffic |\n",
    "| **Confidence gate at 0.70** | Tuned from production data - below 0.70, wrong routing creates more friction than a clarification prompt |\n",
    "| **Registry-driven routes** | Shortcode table lives in `routing-policy.yaml`, not in workflow code. Adding an agent = edit the spec, no workflow rewrite |\n",
    "| **No cross-agent dependencies** | Agents share zero direct connections. All coordination flows through the Orchestrator - enables independent scaling and failure isolation |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Where This Pattern Transfers\n",
    "\n",
    "| Domain | Application |\n",
    "|--------|-------------|\n",
    "| **Customer support** | Route tickets to billing/tech/returns by intent before escalating to human agent |\n",
    "| **Internal tooling** | Slash-command shortcuts for developer ops; LLM fallback for freeform queries |\n",
    "| **E-commerce chatbots** | Deterministic paths for order status/tracking; LLM for product discovery |\n",
    "| **HR / IT helpdesk** | Policy keyword matching for FAQs; LLM for edge cases |\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Section 6 - Production Guardrails\n",
    "\n",
    "| Layer | Rule | Source |\n",
    "|-------|------|--------|\n",
    "| Confidence gate | Score < 0.70 \u2192 clarification, never blind routing | `specs/verification-policy.yaml` |\n",
    "| Shortcode bypass | Deterministic match skips confidence check entirely | `specs/routing-policy.yaml` |\n",
    "| Error recovery | Failed agent executions route to self-healing Error Handler | Error Handler workflow |\n",
    "| Anti-hallucination | Critical Analyst applies `[Inference]` / `[Unverified]` labels on complex queries | Verification protocol |\n",
    "| Registry-only IDs | No sheet IDs or credentials hardcoded in workflows | `data/sheet_registry.json` |"
   ]
  },
